<author><name><![CDATA[neilbaldwin]]></name></author>
<updated>2010-06-23T13:38:55-07:00</updated>
<published>2010-06-23T13:38:55-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6515&amp;p=63266#p63266</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6515&amp;p=63266#p63266"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Changing Palette Multiple Times During Refresh]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6515&amp;p=63266#p63266"><![CDATA[
I put a bit more time in on this tonight and got the timing code into a more usable form (though it still needs a bit of tweaking as you'll see). This time I'm doing all 8 splits (well, 7) to make the whole grid animatable. I also programmed two crude animations - one cycles all the colours of the matrix from start to end, left to right. The other animates a spiral that radiates from the centre outwards. I put a simple timer in to periodically switch between the two.<br /><br />One cool thing I figured out is that if I got the timing tight enough, I could squeeze the vertical gaps between the blocks enough to get an extra row of blocks (the NES resolution is 256 x 240 so doing 32 x 32 pixel blocks only gives you enough vertical height for 7 rows). Therefore, it's now a proper 8 x 8 grid! <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://dl.dropbox.com/u/5493868/litewall3.nes">http://dl.dropbox.com/u/5493868/litewall3.nes</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3896">neilbaldwin</a> — Wed Jun 23, 2010 1:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
